# Python Tooling

## Package Manager — uv

Use **uv** for all new Python projects. Never use bare `pip`, `pip-tools`, or `poetry` for new projects.

```bash
# New project
uv init my-project && cd my-project

# Add dependencies
uv add fastapi sqlalchemy[asyncio] pydantic-settings
uv add --dev ruff pytest pytest-asyncio httpx ty

# Run without activating venv
uv run pytest
uv run python -m myapp

# Sync after pulling (replaces pip install -r requirements.txt)
uv sync
```

`uv` manages the virtualenv automatically — no `python -m venv`, `pip install`, or `pyenv virtualenv` needed.

| Don't | Do instead |
|---|---|
| `pip install -r requirements.txt` | `uv sync` |
| `pip install fastapi` | `uv add fastapi` |
| `pip install -e .` | `uv sync` (editable by default) |

## Linting & Formatting — ruff

Use **ruff** for all Python linting and formatting. Configuration lives in `pyproject.toml`:

```toml
[tool.ruff]
line-length = 120

[tool.ruff.format]
quote-style = "double"

[tool.ruff.lint]
select = ["E", "F", "I", "UP"]   # pycodestyle, pyflakes, isort, pyupgrade
```

Always run via `just`:
```
just lint      # ruff check .
just format    # ruff format .
just fix       # ruff check --fix . && ruff format .
```

Never mix ruff with flake8, black, or isort — ruff replaces all three.

## Type Checking — ty

Use **ty** (Astral) for static type checking. Configuration in `pyproject.toml`:

```toml
[tool.ty]
# strict mode recommended for new code
```

Run via `just`:
```
just typecheck   # ty check .
```

All new Python code must be fully typed. Annotate function signatures and return types; no bare `Any` without a comment explaining why.

```python
# ❌ untyped
def fetch_user(user_id):
    return db.get(user_id)

# ✅ typed
def fetch_user(user_id: int) -> User | None:
    return db.get(user_id)
```
